OL,3,CMum glassed man in 'random' attack
OL,4,Coutside pub
OL,6,FKimari Storey, prosecuting, described
OL,7,Fthe attack as "random and unprovoked"
OL,8,Fand told the court the man suffered a
OL,9,F12cm wound to his face and he needed
OL,10,F15 stitches.
OL,12,F"There was grave but not life-
OL,13,Fthreatening injury caused," she said.
OL,15,FThe court heard the victim had been
OL,16,Fleft with recurring pain in his jaw
OL,17,Fwhich felt like an "electric shock".
OL,19,F"I lost a lot of blood and was very
OL,20,Fweak for some time after," the man
OL,21,Fsaid.
